overview: Twin sisters Leslie Davis and Lyndsay Lamb have a knack for helping desperate homeowners sell their lifeless homes; the sisters make necessary, impactful renovations that convert unlovable houses into diamonds in the rough.

episodes.name: Old House to Sold House
episodes.overview: The twins work their design magic to sell a couple's historic bungalow.

episodes.name: Road House to Show House
episodes.overview: Leslie and Lyndsay help a family struggling to sell their roadside rambler. Hoping to distract buyers from the road noise outside, the twins make some bold design choices to turn the dated ranch house into a stylish home that a new family will love.

episodes.name: Condo Cleanup
episodes.overview: A young millennial's recent home improvement projects have made it hard for her to sell her condo. Twins Leslie and Lyndsay transform her DIY disaster into a hip, modern home -- perfect for a first-time home buyer.

episodes.name: Moving Sale Makeover
episodes.overview: A couple is moving out of state for work and needs Leslie and Lyndsay's help to sell their home. The twins revamp their outdated ranch with a modern farmhouse style designed to reel in buyers who love to entertain.

episodes.name: Rental Property Reno
episodes.overview: Leslie and Lyndsay renovate a rental in a budget-friendly, eclectic style.

episodes.name: Starter Home Transformation
episodes.overview: Leslie and Lyndsay update a small home with Scandinavian design elements.

episodes.name: Empty Nest to Family Retreat
episodes.overview: Leslie and Lyndsay transform a dated '90s property into a coastal retreat.

episodes.name: Rough Rambler Reno
episodes.overview: Leslie and Lyndsay must figure out how to price a home without comps.

episodes.name: Split-Level Struggle
episodes.overview: Lyndsay and Leslie update a split-level with modern, minimalist touches.

episodes.name: Lake House Update
episodes.overview: A woman who cares for her ailing father struggles to sell her home in a desirable neighborhood; Leslie and Lyndsay work to transform the outdated property into an industrial-chic showpiece that's perfect for a high-end buyer.

episodes.name: Keeping the Character
episodes.overview: A young couple having trouble selling their older home ask Lyndsay and Leslie for help. The twins are challenged to keep the house's cozy character and add more charm to an aging property that's seen years of mish-mashed styles

episodes.name: Two-Bedroom Dilemma
episodes.overview: Siblings struggle to sell their sister's home need Lyndsay and Leslie's expertise. The twins redefine the dated two-bedroom rambler into a modern three-bedroom farmhouse with a deck that will be Android even on a rainy Pacific Northwestern day.

episodes.name: Small House Save
episodes.overview: Recently divorced, Marty asks Leslie and Lyndsay to assist in selling his small home. They try to give him functionality to every space, mixing Boho style with a bit of Southwest flair to pull in younger buyers.

episodes.name: Mid-Mod Oasis
episodes.overview: A homeowner seeks Leslie and Lyndsay's help to sell her inconsistently style midcentury modern house. By decking out a dreamy nackyard oasis and trimming trees to show off the water and mountain vista, the twins clear the way for a high sale price.

episodes.name: Nest Egg Reno
episodes.overview: A daughter begs Leslie and Lyndsay to take over her mother's rambler after it sat on the market for 3 months. Using a few of their tricks, the twins change its dated and choppy layout by opening up the home and giving it a calming, coastal vibe.

episodes.name: Sibling Split Level
episodes.overview: Contractor Jeff's sister and brother-in-law want to move into their forever home, but they need to get their split-level off the market. With a generous sibling discount and some creativity, Leslie and Lyndsay turn the home into a French country cottage.

episodes.name: Outdated to Upgraded
episodes.overview: Lyndsay and Leslie execute their vision to entice high-end buyers to an outdated rambler. They unveiled the home's hidden potential by opening up the floor plan and decorating it with transitional style throughout, leading to an unbelievable offer.

episodes.name: A Contemporary Cleanup
episodes.overview: After his semi-hoarder house in a prime location sat on the market for months, it's getting handed over to the reluctant sisters. Lyndsay and Leslie transform problems into possibilities as they give this lackluster split level a contemporary facelift.

episodes.name: Historic Home Rescue
episodes.overview: An overwhelmed woman needs Lyndsay and Leslie's help after her mother's home has sat on the market for months. Restoring the 1906 home to its original charm becomes their passion project as they expose its classic character with a cozy-chic cottage feel.

episodes.name: Rough Rental Reno
episodes.overview: Selling their rental home is the only thing preventing a couple from starting their daughter's college fund, but it's in rough shape. Leslie and Lyndsay take a stab at transforming the worn-out house into a sophisticated showplace for first-time buyers.

episodes.name: Nineties to Now
episodes.overview: After sitting on the market for months, a couple's dated tract home urgently needs Lyndsay and Leslie's help. Competing with new builds in the area, they update the home with a high-end cabin look and a new feel that brings in offers WAY over the asking price.

episodes.name: Day Care Redo
episodes.overview: A woman that operates a day care out of her house is having trouble selling since buyers can't visualize her business as a family home. Lyndsay and Leslie transition commercial space back into a cozy residence with a vintage farmhouse style.

episodes.name: Renewed Ocean Views
episodes.overview: A woman is overwhelmed with trying to sell her mom's underwhelming condo. Lyndsay and Leslie step into reinvent condo living by remodeling the space for mature buyers with a modern Mediterranean design that showcases its stunning oean view.

episodes.name: Family Fixer
episodes.overview: Lyndsay and Leslie's cousin can't seem to sell his home, and between the unfinished projects and wild walls, it's easy to see why; the twins aim to bring in a natural style that will fit the neighbourhood, but a rotten surprise may bust their budget.

episodes.name: Old Friends, New Upgrades
episodes.overview: A couple of high school sweethearts turn to their friends Lyndsay and Leslie to help sell their old tri-level home in a neighbourhood of new builds; the twins update the home with a warm minimalist style; Lyndsay makes plans with her own sweetheart.

episodes.name: Million Dollar Design
episodes.overview: Leslie and Lyndsay are on a mission to convert a couple's sprawling home into a nest egg; seeing the potential for a big sale, they use all their tricks to give the massive rooms with wood features and dated mirrors a modern, luxurious overhaul.

episodes.name: Retro Reno
episodes.overview: A military family is overwhelmed trying to sell the cozy, older house that they haven't lived in for almost 15 years; Lyndsay and Leslie use their remodeling tricks to turn this cottage rental into a gorgeous starter home with a stylish retro feel.

episodes.name: Fancy Farmhouse
episodes.overview: While looking for an old friend, Leslie and Lyndsay meet fellow VW enthusiasts who struggle to sell a house they built 15 years ago; the twins update the home's builder-grade materials and add darker finishes for an elegant twist on farmhouse style.

episodes.name: Cottage Vibe
episodes.overview: Three generations of women are eager to sell their over-customized and unfinished 1950s rambler before they find a new place near the ocean; Lyndsay and Leslie introduce the zen-like qualities of cottagecore style to create a cosy home like no other.

episodes.name: Fixing a Cheap Flip
episodes.overview: With her daughter's dire health crisis alleviated, a mother is ready to part with a 1920s bungalow she bought to be by her side.

episodes.name: Five Days to List
episodes.overview: A widow and her son need help to give their 14-room Victorian farmhouse a more broad appeal.

episodes.name: Honorary Junior Designer
episodes.overview: A woman and her husband seek to honor her late father's legacy by restoring her childhood home.

episodes.name: Selling a Well-Loved Home
episodes.overview: Lyndsay and Leslie take over the reins to help a father part ways with his family home.

episodes.name: A New Place Like Home
episodes.overview: A couple loves the neighborhood where they've raised three kids,but they've grown tired of their house of over 20 years.

episodes.name: Sell With a Kiss
episodes.overview: After helping friends settle into a new and larger family home, Lyndsay and Leslie take on their former place.

episodes.name: A Doctor's Oasis
episodes.overview: Lyndsay and Leslie help a busy doctor increase the equity on her newly purchased condo and transform it into a serene oasis.

episodes.name: Hygge Bad Pipe Dream
episodes.overview: Lyndsay and Leslie aid a retiring woman by selling her condo with a cozy Euro-style update, but the mood dampens when a ticking time bomb of a plumbing issue rears its head.

episodes.name: A First House to a Future Sale?
episodes.overview: A couple have been in their starter home for 20 years and are ready to move out and up, but the numbers have them looking at their current house with new eyes.

episodes.name: A Tricky Listing
episodes.overview: Market factors cause Lyndsay and Leslie to increase their investment for a landlord couple trying to sell their nearly $1 million duplex.

episodes.name: Worst House Gains Big Equity
episodes.overview: Lyndsay and Leslie help a young couple get a major return on their investment for their new midcentury modern home.

episodes.name: To Move or Not to Move
episodes.overview: A couple who are staples of their community are ready for a home renovation, but she's more excited about the change than he is. Lyndsay and Leslie step in to get her the updated space she wants while retaining all the qualities he seeks to keep.

episodes.name: Bittersweet Sale
episodes.overview: Upon learning a dear member of their team needs to sell her house in a hurry, Lyndsay and Leslie jump into action, promising to forgo any profit to help their BFF.
